---
/**
 * Singleton `aria-live` region — announces dynamic state changes to screen
 * readers. Mount exactly once, as the last child of `<body>` in BaseLayout.
 *
 * Writers call `announce()` from `src/lib/a11y/announce.ts`; that helper
 * looks up `#a11y-announcer` by id and sets its text content.
 *
 * Why `aria-live="polite"` by default: assertive interrupts the user, which
 * is rarely what we want. Callers that need interruption pass
 * `announce(msg, { assertive: true })` and the helper flips the attribute
 * before writing.
 */
---

<div
  id="a11y-announcer"
  class="sr-only"
  aria-live="polite"
  aria-atomic="true"
  role="status"
></div>
